args: I've been trying all sorts of pranks, but\nnothing seems to be working. Maybe I'm\njust not cut out for the prankster life...
But I can't let that get me down. I'm gonna\nbe a bad boy, no matter what!
Maybe I should try being naughty in ways\nthat don't involve pranks?
Hmmm... What does that mean, though?
Treats, treats, treats, to eat, eat, eat!\nI've got treats for you Lowen!
Um...is something wrong? \nYou're staring pretty hard.
You look distraught, and I'd like you to be\ndis-NOT!
Ha ha, okay, you caught me.\nI AM a little distraught.
Mhmm. My many years watching over the\nchoir children has given me something of a\nsixth sense when it comes to these things.
Ah, right. I guess that makes sense.
Did you ever have any...bad kids?\nI've been wondering what exactly\nmakes a bad kid bad.
All of my children are angels, though there\nHAVE been a few that liked to play hooky!

It affects the whole choir when one or two
voices are missing, so whenever someone
skipped practice I'd have to give 'em the
'ol tsk-tsk!
Hm, I wonder where Lowen is. We were\nsupposed to do some training.
Heh heh, who cares about training?\nIt's hard, and it makes me sore!
I'm only doing ONE thing today,\nand that's PLAYING!
Are you sure you ought to be skipping\npractice?
I'm Sweet Lowen, the part of you that's\na good little boy.
You know you won't grow up big and strong\nif you don't train, right?
...Wait, that's all it took to convince you?\nI thought you were supposed to be\nBad-Boy Lowen!
I am, but I can't argue with facts. The only\nreason I've gotten stronger is because\nI've been training.
So it would be pretty silly to stop now,\nright?
Well sure, but... Hold on, are you saying\nyou don't want to be a bad boy anymore?
Oh, butterscotch! Hey, do you know\nhow I can be a bad boy?
Clearly I'm desperate here! Come on,\nwe'll work it out together.
Well... What if we actually DID skip\npractice, like we're doing right now?
Okaaay, how about we steal some food\nthen?
But then I'll be too full for dinner...
What if we stay up super late?
Why does it feel like I'M the bad version\nof me right now?!
Rrgh. Fine. This is my last suggestion.\nIf you made Louise cry, that would\nDEFINITELYâ€”
Are you nuts?! I could never be that mean!
She's the most important person in the\nworld to me.
I would never make her sad on purpose!
Yeah, me neither. You're giving up on the\nwhole bad boy thing, then?
You better get to practice, so you can get\nstrong and protect Louise!
Yeah! I gotta work hard and get strong!
I better hustle over and say sorry to\nthe prince. Bye!
See? It'll never work! I'll NEVER become\na bad boy!
Um, Lowen? Why are you yelling at me?
Ugh... I don't want to make Louise cry,\nbut I have to be bad SOMEHOW!
Why is being naughty so hard?!
Wh-whoa there kiddo. I don't know what\nyou're talking about, but let's calm down!
